<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/28602ANLPVHQNKPKMTKMVBQPLMHBQTNGH> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "SPOTLIGHT: Ballet Kelowna";
  schema:description """
	CANADIAN CONTEMPORARY BALLET<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The <span class=\"ItalicText\">Vividus: Full of Life</span> program features a stunning lineup of signature works from Ballet Kelowna’s contemporary ballet repertoire. With Alysa Pires’ striking <span class=\"ItalicText\">Vestiges</span>, Kirsten Wicklund’s ethereal <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Forever Part</span>, and Guillaume Côté’s electrifying <span class=\"ItalicText\">Le Carnaval des Animaux</span>, this high-energy program from Canada’s leading dancemakers promises to please a wide range of spectators.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Award-winning choreographer Alysa Pires constructs a striking commentary on the search for true connection and meaning amid disorder. Set to the cinematic melodies of violinist Hilary Hahn and composer Hauschka, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Vestiges</span> highlights the virtuosity of Pires’ bold and lively choreography.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Inspired by daydreams and longing, Kirsten Wicklund’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Forever Part</span> is a poignant ensemble piece exploring the inherent tension of the permanence of forever. With rhythmic group sections and stirring duets, this piece meditates on both yearning and desire as well as anxiety and restriction.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rounding out the program, Guillaume Côté, Principal Dancer and Chorographic Associate with The National Ballet of Canada, applies his fresh, artistic vision to a jovial rendition of Camille Saint-Saëns’ <span class=\"ItalicText\">Le Carnaval des Animaux</span>, regarded as one of the French composer’s best-known works. Full of whimsical ornamentation, this upbeat ensemble piece pushes the limits of contemporary ballet and promises to delight audiences with its exuberant energy of frolicking and fun.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Ballet Kelowna's Vancouver-Island debut was on the 2023-2024 Spotlight Season.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">PROGRAMME</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Vestiges</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Choreography:</span> Alysa Pires<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Music:</span> Hilary Hahn and Hauschka<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Lighting Design:</span> Rylee Block<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Costume Concept:</span> Alysa Pires<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Costume Couturier:</span> Colleen Bryant | KOCO<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Pause</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The Forever Part</span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Choreography:</span> Kirsten Wicklund<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Music:</span> J.S. Bach, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Toccata and Fugue in D Minor, Goldberg Variations, BWV 988: Aria da capo</span>, and Kirsten Wicklund<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Lighting Design:</span> Rylee Block<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Costume Concept:</span> Kirsten Wicklund<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Costume Assistants:</span> Lori Lawler and Hazel Rodgers<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Intermission</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Le Carnaval des Animaux</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Choreography:</span> Guillaume Côté<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Music:</span> Camille Saint-Saëns, Le Carnaval des animaux<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Lighting Design:</span> Rylee Block<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Costumes:</span> Christopher Read<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
